<br>
&quot;If you don't see that by now, you are blind.&quot; In other words I am right you are wrong. . . <br>
<br>
Sorry had to say that :-)<br>
<br>
As to the server dieing. Strange, I spend time giving away things to newbies and well ya know I am seeing a lot of newbies a coming up in the world.<br>
<br>
I certainly am not seeing the empty deserted newbie zones that would indicate death from bellow as well as from above.<br>
<br>
What I am seeing is a good few people deleting characters and starting again. You might find that a lot of the folks who vanished from your friends lists are not actually gone but are re born.<br>
<br>
Of course there is a constant attrition as people grow / get bored / have things happen in there life. This is a natural cycle in EQ, one I would guess many of us have been through.<br>
<br>
In terms of grouping, there are definetly 2 pools of people, those under 30 and those over 50. In between those 2 areas is a more quiet period BUT if you get to know lots of people you can get groups. Might mean you have to travel but you can.<br>
<br>
Thought I say you can get groups there is a key alas here to getting a group, that key is being social and out going. The world is sparsley populated, if you do not have a guild for getting groups then you better know a lot of people by name so you can send em tells and see what they are up to.<br>
<br>
Normaly if I want to group I can find folks in a short period of time, in playing with them and their friends I get to know more people and so on.<br>
<br>
Wandering to a dungeon lfg in this server does not work. Karnors is not full of 50+ people with a few looks for more players, last time I looked there where 6. Does kind a make this place BYOG (bring your own group). In that way it seems more like adventure novels where you pick who you are grouping with before you head out in to the unkown.<br>
<br>
To be fair, if you are not obsesively social and not in a guild that has folks your own age then life is going to be rather lonely <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  my advice is to find a guild that fits your age and play with them. Even in a guild you will have to make an effort to get folks to play together but it is worth it.<br>
<br>
As to the folks on your friends list. My list is fully poped with 30 folks and has been since I started, I think only 3 people have really left the game. A few re started but . . .<br>
<br>
So all in all I would say that the server is not dieing, it is lean but damn do I love it the way it is :-) Still I probably have a bias as I play 2 or 3 chars (if my partner is on then I only play 2 chars) and so have access to a default group that can go to most places on its own (druid, monk, enchantress).<br>
<br>
Good luck to you feneant.<br>
<br>
Hugs<br>
<br>
Intra Treedawn lvl 41 enchantress<br>
Sena Treedawn lvl 41 monket<br>
