Intra <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numtini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 12:03:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=47>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> I just blundered into this topic. If I could just offer my two cents as an outsider about why I don't play on FV.<br>
<br>
First of all, I was a big supporter of it. But Verant's nonsense about cancelling the RP aspect, then putting it back sort of, really turned me off. It seemed to me that I was being played by VI to keep me in the game and once they had done that for as long as they could, they pulled the rug out. That combined with a lot of anti-RPers on this board before server release really turned me off of the whole thing. When the server came up, I decided to wait until it got a little less crowded. DAOC came out with a real RP ruleset and I went there, but DAOC once again proved the rule that PVP=Griefers and I came back to EQ. But I never got around to actually joining FV.<br>
<br>
Looking at it now, first and foremost, I'm already frustrated on a regular server with my ability to get groups. I don't have that long on a given day to play and I play some odd hours. The population on FV is very small with the languages and inability to do zonewides, and the forced anon making LFG pretty useless, and the grouping restrictions, it just seems like it would be a nightmare to get groups. <br>
<br>
The rules are the rules. I still don't see how any of them promote roleplaying at all. Mostly they just seem to introduce more frustration into a game that already has a lot of frustration elements. Languages may be a RP thing, but that seems like something to be powergamed over -- and I see suggestions on making learning multiple languages a priority. If that's the solution, what's the point anyway? Tho I suppose this would be a harmless enough rule to keep the d00dieheads off the server.<br>
<br>
And I can tell you that from the outside, it sure looks like the server is dying. And it makes me think, gee, why do I want to create a character there and never find a group and watch my friends drift away to other servers.<br>
<br>
What would it take for me to move to the server? Well, if they made more than a token overture to RPers it would improve my mood towards the server--I still entertain notions that VI created an unplayable server ruleset in order to demonstrate that RPers are not a real market. If they got rid of the stupid RP/anon tag, which serves no purpose other than to force people to ask OOC questions and make it harder to find groups, that would actually do a lot to make me think it was a viable server.<br>
<br>
But I guess that's the big issue. I don't see FV as a viable server.<br>
<br>
Remember this is an outsider's view, so please don't shoot the messenger. I've never played on FV, other than logging in to reserve my name when the thing first came up. My perceptions may not be accurate, but they are my perceptions and if we're talking about why people don't play on the server, that's the real issue. <p><table border=0 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0><tr><td><img src="http://home.tampabay.rr.com/legolaas/images/numtini-100.jpg" width="52" height="100"></td><td><table style="font-family:verdana,arial;" border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;"><A HREF="http://pub94.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN" title="<insert popup caption here>" style="color:#ff0000;font-weight:700;">Numtini Lightheart</A></td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;">45th Season Gnome of Death</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;">Member, <A HREF="http://pub96.ezboard.com/beqcivismacto" title="Civis Macto Website" style="color:#ff0000;">Civis Macto</A></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
