<br>
As to the server dying, you are pretty much wrong.  Sorry.  Just as some people say the earth is overpopulated, its the same principle.  It's not population, it's population density that is of concern.  As the server ages, the server becomes striated in different PC level ranges, and with all the expansions, people in level ranges are distributed much thinner than in the lower levels.  <br>
<br>
I am fairly new to the server, I came here AFTER luclin launched.  I have met many other people that also came to FV after Luclin, as I group with them almost daily.  Okay, so some of your friends left, I'm sorry to hear it.  But why the doomsaying?  The server isn't dying, and it is certianly far from dead.  Keep in mind some players left this server to try out Vah Shir or Beastlords on other servers.  They are, or will likely be, back.  If you count the server opening, which was high-population hell, then sure, the server is quite dead.  But let's look at the server population from a more steady-state population level, and I would say it's probably nearly the same.<br>
<br>
Also, I heard that Brad Mcquaid plays on this server.  As such, I'm sure there are probably other (current) employees that play here also.  If you really want your petitions heard, post on the official websites, rather than ranting here.  &lt;- not a flame, just a suggestion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 284<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 6:42:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I think ..</span><hr size=1> .. we want our suggestions listened to, not just heard.  The people here can't do anything about what we say, but we all do read and comment on the ideas.  That's a lot better than being ignored.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you really want your petitions heard, post on the official websites, rather than ranting here. &lt;- not a flame, just a suggestion.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->We all know posting on the VI board, /bug, and /feedback are ignored.  OTH, the latest patch has absolutely floored me.  It's as if someone in Verant opened up the /bug and /feedback bins and started fixing things.  It's only taken them two years, but wow, what a patch! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 8:27:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionav