<br>
The problem is that frustrations run high with the restrictions, when you have a language barrier, shout limitations and Anon on all at the same time, it becomes impossible to organize.  We also have to remember that Verant sits around all day long and thinks of ways of making this game challenging to people, and what might be good for the 30 other servers might not work well with the specialized few.  <br>
<br>
If Shout were enabled blue and you could reach the whole zone, grouping would be easier, the language barrier is tiresome and frustrating but realistic and I wouldn't change it (Plus my character has really used it to his advantage).  The Anon was to keep us from reverting, something we are going to do anyway but I think it is an open ended question not easily answered, but with at least Shout fixed, we could survive easier without affecting gameplay.  <br>
<br>
We can all pat ourselves on the backs as say FV is doing okay, or we can grab Kleenex and lament the sad loss of our server, either way, until Verant pulls it, it is here and so am I.  The fact remains that player dissatisfaction is high and the turn over rate is high.  I see lots of people cheating on language learning to get by part of the problems and they are destroying the RPing part to make life easier.  That is the crime.<br>
